---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About Palchat">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="app-container">
      <header style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-6);">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">About</p>
        <h1 class="section-title" style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-top: var(--sp-2);">
          Palchat is a playground of product ideas and tiny tools.
        </h1>
        <p class="body-text" style="max-width: 640px; margin-top: var(--sp-3);">
          It is intentionally <span style="font-weight: 600;">not</span> a chat tool. The goal is to collect opinionated
          ideas and pair them with small, free utilities that help builders decide what to work on next.
        </p>
      </header>

      <section class="section-tight" style="padding-top: 0; padding-bottom: var(--sp-6);">
        <h2 class="section-title">
          What Palchat tries to do
        </h2>
        <ul class="body-text" style="margin-top: var(--sp-3);">
          <li style="display: flex; gap: var(--sp-2); margin-bottom: var(--sp-2);">
            <span
              style="margin-top: 6px; width: 6px; height: 6px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--color-text-secondary); flex-shrink: 0;"
            />
            <span><span style="font-weight: 500;">Collect useful ideas</span> — focused on products that solo builders or small teams can realistically ship.</span>
          </li>
          <li style="display: flex; gap: var(--sp-2); margin-bottom: var(--sp-2);">
            <span
              style="margin-top: 6px; width: 6px; height: 6px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--color-text-secondary); flex-shrink: 0;"
            />
            <span><span style="font-weight: 500;">Offer tiny SaaS-style tools</span> — simple utilities (like the Idea Prioritization Tool) that are free to use in the browser.</span>
          </li>
          <li style="display: flex; gap: var(--sp-2);">
            <span
              style="margin-top: 6px; width: 6px; height: 6px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--color-text-secondary); flex-shrink: 0;"
            />
            <span><span style="font-weight: 500;">Stay low-friction</span> — no logins required for core exploration, no feeds, no infinite scrolling.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="section-tight" style="padding-top: 0; padding-bottom: var(--sp-6);">
        <h2 class="section-title">
          Tech stack
        </h2>
        <p class="body-text" style="margin-top: var(--sp-3);">
          Palchat is built with a simple, scalable stack that makes it easy to add more ideas and tools over time.
        </p>

        <div class="card" style="margin-top: var(--sp-4); display: grid; gap: var(--sp-4);">
          <div>
            <h3 class="section-title" style="font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: var(--sp-2);">
              At a glance
            </h3>
            <ul class="body-text-small">
              <li>Astro for fast, modern pages.</li>
              <li>React (via <code>@astrojs/react</code>) for interactive components when needed.</li>
              <li>Tailwind CSS for utility classes layered on top of design tokens.</li>
              <li>PostgreSQL with a pooled client and managed hosting.</li>
              <li>Vercel for hosting, SSL, and deployments.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--sp-3); justify-content: space-between;">
            <p class="body-text-small">
              For a more visual breakdown of how these pieces fit together (by layer: UI, APIs, data, and infra), you can
              see the dedicated tech stack page.
            </p>
            <a href="/tech-stack" class="btn btn-secondary" style="align-self: flex-start;">
              View full tech stack
              <span aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 0.75rem; margin-left: 4px;">→</span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section-tight" style="padding-top: 0;">
        <h2 class="section-title">
          Get in touch
        </h2>
        <p class="body-text" style="margin-top: var(--sp-3);">
          If you have an idea that might fit here—or a tiny tool you wish existed—reach out and it might make its way
          into Palchat.
        </p>
        <p class="body-text-small">
          You can email <a href="mailto:hello@palchat.org" class="footer-link">hello@palchat.org</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
